sec.p:
LC can be seen as a latent condition emerging after infection that in turn affects the onset or persistence of long-term symptoms. In this context, let Y be a binary indicator for the presence of LC and A be a binary indicator for history of infection. We know that individuals without a history of infection cannot have LC. We formalize this with the condition as \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
