First, we applied the Lasso-penalized LCRI methodology with balancing weights defined as in Eq. (4) using 30 strata defined by age (18–45, 46–65, >65), sex (male, female), and race (non-Hispanic Asian, non-Hispanic Black, non-Hispanic White, Hispanic, Mixed race/other/missing). This represents a core set of adjustment variables, though unmeasured confounding may still be present. In the original LCRI manuscript these variables were also included as possible model covariates, but were not selected by the Lasso penalization, and differences in model coefficients were negligible, so we presently consider these covariates via balancing weighting only, i.e., \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
